macchanger
MAC address changer for network interfaces

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
macchanger is a utility for viewing and manipulating the MAC address of network interfaces. Useful for network anonymity and bypassing MAC filtering.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which macchanger
Install command:

sudo apt install macchanger
Basic Syntax
macchanger [options] <interface>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
macchanger -s eth0

Show current MAC	View MAC address	
sudo macchanger -r eth0

Random MAC	Randomize MAC	
sudo macchanger -m XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX eth0

Set specific MAC	Impersonate device	
sudo macchanger -p eth0

Reset to permanent	Restore original	
sudo macchanger -a eth0

Same vendor random	Keep vendor prefix	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Bring interface down: sudo ifconfig eth0 down
2
Change MAC: sudo macchanger -r eth0
3
Bring interface up: sudo ifconfig eth0 up
4
Verify: macchanger -s eth0
Understanding the Output
Shows current, permanent, and new MAC addresses.

Important Warnings
•
Interface must be down before changing
•
MAC spoofing may violate policies
•
Resets on reboot by default
